### 3. Refresh token (requires valid token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 4. Get all users (protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 5. Get user by ID (protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 6. Update user (protected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "username": "updated_owner",
  "email": "owner_updated@example.com"
}

### 7. Change password (protected)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/1/password
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "old_password": "secure123",
  "new_password": "newpass456"
}

### 8. Create a pet (protected)
